One main difference this time is I’ve handed over the keys to someone else. A friend — and experienced runner — who is guiding me through the process. Left to my own devices, I tend to alternate between overtraining, under-believing, and ignoring all evidence in favour of whatever romantic training idea is currently floating through my brain. So this time, I’m trying structure. Consistency. Restraint. (I give that three weeks, tops.)

So here we are: 13 weeks out. The beginning stages of… I don’t know if I’ll run sub-3 again. But I’ll document the attempt, the process, and the data that drips out along the way. I’m choosing to believe if only for a little while, and at least in this moment it seems worth leaning into. 

Let’s see what happens.
